hen one fingertip then no hands.";i:1;s:44:"Then do exercise with eyes closed if steady.";i:2;s:40:"Holding onto table or chair for balance.";i:3;s:64:"Slowly bend one knee toward chest without bending waist or hips.";i:4;s:31:"Hold position for 5-10 seconds.";i:5;s:34:"Slowly lower leg all the way down.";i:6;s:22:"Repeat with other leg.";i:7;s:169:"The exercises below were selected to help your neuropathy no matter what the cause is but it is only a best guess and not an actual prescription based on an examination.";i:8;s:57:"Start by sitting in a firm chair ideally without armrest.";i:9;s:26:"Scoot towards the edge of.";i:10;s:66:"Exercises for Peripheral Neuropathy Bipedal Toe and Heel Raises 1.";i:11;s:78:"Stand in front of a counter table or chair that is at the level of your waist.";i:12;s:36:"Move your feet shoulder-width apart.";i:13;s:34:"Rise up on the balls of your feet.";i:14;s:33:"Hold this position for 5 seconds.";i:15;s:35:"Slowly return to starting position.";i:16;s:24:"Rock back on your heels.";i:17;s:33:"Hold this position for 5 seconds.";i:18;s:27:"Sit on the edge of a chair.";i:19;s:60:"Extend one leg in front of you with your toe pointed upward.";i:20;s:56:"Bend the opposite knee with your foot flat on the floor.";i:21;s:100:"Position your chest over your straight leg and straighten your back until you feel a muscle stretch.";i:22;s:37:"Hold this position for 15 20 seconds.";i:23;s:39:"Sit at the edge of a chair or your bed.";i:24;s:69:"Tuck your chin down to your chest and put your arms behind your back.";i:25;s:98:"Slouch over by leaning forward as far as you can go without causing an increase in your back pain.";i:26;s:58:"Pull your toe back towards your nose as far as you can go.";i:27;s:74:"Slowly straighten your knee until you feel a pull in the back of your leg.";i:28;s:51:"Side leg raises are great exercises for neuropathy.";i:29;s:82:"Once again using the support of a counter or chair steady yourself using one hand.";i:30;s:60:"Stand upright with your feet slightly apart from each other.";i:31;s:51:"Now slowly raise your one leg to the side and hold.";i:32;s:339:"Chair exercise basics dvd Share This diabetes exercises disease of the nerves exercises for the feet and hands finger exercises nerve damage neuropathy neuropathy and exercise proprioception exercises Sit and Be Fit small ball exercises for the feet small ball exercises for the hands somatosensory system tactile stimulation and exercise.";i:33;s:24:"Use a chair for support.";i:34;s:65:"Keep your hands on the top of the chair throughout the exercises.";i:35;s:36:"Lift both heels up and down 8 times.";i:36;s:38:"Pull your abdomen in while doing this.";i:37;s:93:"Keep pulling your abdomen in as you lift one heel keeping the ball of the foot on the ground.";i:38;s:44:"Place the heel down and then lift the other.";i:39;s:53:"The ReBuilder cures neuropathy for the vast majority.";i:40;s:169:"The ReBuilders patented electrical stimulation dedvice has been proven 94 effective in recent clinical studies in reducing and even REVERSING the symptoms of neuropathy.";i:41;s:90:"Unlike common TENS devices that merely block pain signals the ReBuilder does the opposite.";i:42;s:75:"The ReBuilder opens up the nerve paths and re-educates them so that normal.";i:43;s:38:"Foot and Leg Exercises for Neuropathy.";i:44;s:22:"By Mary Ann Wilson RN.";i:45;s:91:"Here are some great foot and leg exercises for anyone managing the condition of neuropathy.";i:46;s:51:"These exercises can be done from a seated position.";i:47;s:76:"Move to the front edge of the chair and firmly plant the feet on the ground.";i:48;s:50:"Try Out These 5 Leg Foot Exercises For Neuropathy.";i:49;s:40:"For this exercise you will need a chair.";i:50;s:28:"Sit on it close to the edge.";i:51;s:108:"Lift one leg point the toe and extend it out in front of you while keeping the other foot flat on the floor.";i:52;s:57:"Now lean over until your chest touches your straight leg.";i:53;s:38:"Keep your back as straight as you can.";i:54;s:148:"The Why Recent studies have found that the slow graceful exercises of Qigong - which originated centuries ago in China as a martial art can improve.";i:55;s:92:"Exercises that incorporate movement and breathing may be beneficial for neuropathy patients.";i:56;s:59:"The routine can be for 15 to 30 minutes a few times a week.";i:57;s:174:"Your loved one doesnt need to attend formal classes walks or bike rides help to increase range and strength of movement in muscles and improve pulmonary and cardiac function.";i:58;s:55:"Yes exercise can help neuropathy and heal nerve damage.";i:59;s:173:"People suffering from peripheral neuropathy which causes pain numbness tingling and burning sensation in the arms legs hands and feet should perform strengthening exercises.";i:60;s:99:"Strengthening exercises can improve muscle strength in people suffering from peripheral neuropathy.";i:61;s:44:"Join us for a demonstration of Chair QiGong.";i:62;s:159:"QiGong combines gentle flowing movement with breathing and meditation techniques that provide low impact exercise improved balance and overall health benefits.";i:63;s:117:"Cynthia Maltenfort who is a yoga tai chi and QiGong instructor will lead us in this ancient form of Chinese exercise.";i:64;s:117:"Rocking chair exercise is a great way of getting clarity into what you want from life and what really matters to you.";i:65;s:36:"It is short and easy yet quite deep.";i:66;s:49:"Cardiovascular exercise in a chair or wheelchair.";i:67;s:214:"Chair aerobics a series of seated repetitive movements will raise your heart rate and help you burn calories as will many strength training exercises when performed at a fast pace with a high number of repetitions.";i:68;s:166:"Horseback riding may not be the first exercise that comes to mind for neuropathy patients but it has proven to be an effective workout for people with this condition.";i:69;s:115:"Horseback riding requires the use of certain muscles yet the foot muscles are relatively relaxed during this sport.";i:70;s:152:"Yoga poses including the plank and bridge poses recommended by my physical therapist caused pain so with great disappointment I stopped practicing yoga.";i:71;s:142:"Id already stopped swimming and playing tennis due to impingement syndrome in my right shoulder which my physical therapy hadnt helped either.";i:72;s:45:"My exercise options dwindled down to walking.";i:73;s:103:"Doctors can recommend an exercise plan that will reduce neuropathy pain and control blood sugar levels.";i:74;s:58:"Patients should also quit smoking and eat healthful meals.";i:75;s:115:"Massages of hands and feet may also aid neuropathy management by stimulating nerves and temporarily relieving pain.";}}